notes: Annual average of quarterly worker turnover rates. Worker turnover is a measure of the number of people starting and finishing jobs in a quarter, relative to the total number of jobs. A lower worker turnover indicates more stability. Data may be suppressed for some regions in some years. Results are subject to large sample errors, especially in smaller regions.
A percentage point (pp) is the unit for the arithmetic difference of two percentages.
